btrplace.model.view

Class ShareableResource

  • java.lang.Object
    • btrplace.model.view.ShareableResource
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ModelView, Cloneable

    public class ShareableResource
extends Object
implements ModelView, Cloneable
    A view to denote a resource that nodes share among the VMs they host

    The view allows to specify the physical resource capacity of the nodes and the amount of virtual resources allocated to the VMs.

    Associated constraints:

    • Preserve to ensure the availability of a certain amount of virtual resources for a VM
    • ResourceCapacity to cap the amount of physical resources that can be used on a node
    • Overbook to specify a mapping between the virtual and the physical resources.

    By default, if there is no Preserve constraint for a VM, it is considered the VM requires the same amount of virtual resources it is currently consuming.

    By default, if there is no Overbook constraint for a node, a conservative ratio of 1 is used. This means one unit of virtual resources consumes one unit of physical resources.

    Author:
    Fabien Hermenier
